      <guid>https://input-output-hk.github.io/adrestia/docs/common-use-cases/how-to-make-a-transaction/</guid>
      <description>using cardano-wallet Assuming you have already created a wallet, you can send a transaction by using the following endpoint:
POST /v2/byron-wallets/{walletId}/transactions
Behind the scene, the wallet engine will select necessary inputs from the wallet, generate a change address within the wallet, sign and submit the transaction. A transaction can have multiple outputs, possibly to the same address. Note that in Byron, addresses are necessarily base58-encoded (as an enforced convention).</description>
